    <item>
      <title>Kubernetes Dashboard</title>
      <link>https://blinkeye.github.io/post/public/2019-05-30-kubernetes-dashboard/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 21 May 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://blinkeye.github.io/post/public/2019-05-30-kubernetes-dashboard/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;If you ever worked with the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/kubernetes/dashboard&#34;&gt;Kubernetes Dashboard&lt;/a&gt; you certainly have noticed the rather short session timeout (about 10 minutes).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By adjusting the startup parameters you can either:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Increase the timeout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disable the timeout&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skip authentication altogether&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Skipping the authentication is useful in a dev environment where you don&amp;rsquo;t need or want authentication.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
